While using boto3 in AWS the documentation of the SSM call start_automation_execution does not seem to match with the ui of that part. And trying the code like:

    response = ssm_client.start_automation_execution(
        DocumentName=document_name,
        Mode='Auto',
        Parameters={
            'InstanceId': [  ]
        },
        TargetParameterName='InstanceId',
        Targets=[
            {
                'Key': 'tag:InstanceUuid',
                'Values': [
                    f"value:{instance_uuid}"
                ]
            }
        ]
    )

Produces an error:
Internal processing error: An error occurred (InvalidAutomationExecutionParametersException) when calling the StartAutomationExecution operation: Target key can have only following values : ParameterValues, ResourceGroup

Which seems to indicate you need to use a ResourceGroup like in the AWS ui. But the documentation is stating something in the direction of the request for the send_command. Which would suit our use case better but does not seem to be supported.

So I guess the documentation (maybe more) needs to be changed to reflect how this request works.

